 
<p>
  European countries are considering a <a href="https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/europe-high-speed-rail-network/index.html">continent-wide high speed rail network</a>.
<p>
  This is a very good thing to do; but to get the full benefit of it, we
  must campaign against demanding ID from each passenger.  Several
  countries, including Spain and Italy, imposed that requirement as a
  measure for tracking Covid-19 cases &mdash; but now that there are so many
  cases, no country in Europe is really trying to find them all.
  That means this anti-freedom policy is no longer justified.

 